item.title: Cant portfoward
item.dc:creator: @_Kate1 ,Kate
item.description:
@_Kate1 wrote:

If you have a router, you have a Default Gateway. Go onto Start, and search CMD. Open it up, and type:

ipconfig /all

A load of stuff comes up, If you scroll up to where it has something to do with your Wireless Connection, you should see your Default Gateway in the list of IPâ€™s. Put that into your address bar- Your Default Gateway is basically the web address for your router page. You can also access your default gateway by putting in your IP address found at:

[ul][li]WhatsMyIp.Org[/li]
[li]IPChicken.Com[/li][/ul]

This is optional for most routers.
